"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s31_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Screening"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"db7551",
"children":[
"Screening"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2b0df6",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"One-time ultrasonographic screening is indicated to detect an asymptomatic ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"abdominal aortic aneurysm",
"children":[
"AAA"
]
},
" in any man between the ages of 65 and 75 years who has ever smoked and in selected men ages 65 to 75 years who have never smoked (e.g., family history of AAA)."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f62bf0",
"children":[
"Do not screen women for AAA."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s31_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"59137a",
"children":[
"Most chronic AAAs are asymptomatic. Signs and symptoms of a ruptured AAA include new abdominal, flank, or back pain; hypotension; syncope; and sudden collapse and shock. The diagnosis is confirmed by ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"magnetic resonance angiography",
"children":[
"MRA"
]
},
" or CT."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"40ac7e",
"children":[
"Ultrasonography is not accurate for diagnosing a ruptured abdominal aorta."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s31_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"449072",
"children":[
"Therapy includes treatment of cardiovascular risk factors. Schedule surgical or endovascular repair of AAAs ≥5.5 cm in diameter, those growing ≥0.5 cm per year, or symptomatic AAAs. Ruptured AAA requires emergent surgery or endovascular repair."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s31_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Follow-up"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b9c20d",
"children":[
"Follow-up"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"85ba70",
"children":[
"Most AAAs are asymptomatic. Abdominal ultrasonography surveillance intervals are based on aortic diameter:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"86f15a",
"children":[
"<4 cm → every 2 to 3 years"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"073ec4",
"children":[
"4.0-5.5 cm → every 6 to 12 months"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
